This is a convenient spot to get your fast food Mexican fix on the run at Millennium Station.  It's fun to sit here and watch the hustle and bustle of the train station.  Good food, clean surroundings and pleasant staff.

Tasty Mexican food with reasonable selection and fast service, located very conveniently on the walkway to the South Shore and Metra Electric trains.  Not world-beating cuisine, perhaps, but a good option when you're rushing for the train.  If you're not rushing, the space is not large, but it is sufficient to sit and get some work done as you enjoy your shrimp quesadilla.

Food price doesn't relate to the less than great quality, but that's what you get when you eat at a well known chain. I have to admit my first time trying Taco Fresco after hearing about it as if it was some magical Mexican restaurant on the west coast that everyone adored...I was disappointed. Average food, service is what you expect (you order it, they cook it). Like most train station restaurants the space is too small for anyone to actually eat there which makes sense since its a business area and most people grab the food and snack while they're working.  They put their cutest on the front line as one reviewer has already said :-)
